summary: An Ordinance authorizing, empowering and directing the Mayor and City Comptroller and ex-officio City Clerk to, in the name of and on behalf of The City of Seattle, enter into a memorandum of agreement with the Puget Sound Electric Railway, a corporation, James A. Ward and Frankie E. Ward, his wife, and Seattle Brewing & Malting Company, a corporation, affecting portions of Juneau Street and Duwamish Avenue and certain property adjacent thereto, and declaring an emergency.
